Introduction
------------

The LEDKonfigurator script allows for the manipulation
in various ways of LEDs on a Linux system including

- Turning LEDs on/off
- Changing the system event trigger for LEDs
- Monitoring the performance of a process and turning
  LEDs on/off according to that performance

Usage
-----

The script is run by executing the
led_konfigurator.sh script. It must be run as a user
with the appropriate privliges or with sudo to have
the approriate privliges.

The script is menu driven and is used by entering
input as prompted by the script.

